theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- First inclusion: `interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A)`
    have h₁ :
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_interior_closure
        (X := X) (A := closure A)
    simpa using h₁
  · -- Second inclusion via `P2` for `interior (closure A)`
    have h₂ : Topology.P2 (X := X) (interior (closure A)) :=
      Topology.P2_interior_closure (X := X) (A := A)
    -- Unfold the definition of `P2`
    have : interior (closure A : Set X) ⊆
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
      simpa [Topology.P2, interior_interior] using h₂
    simpa using this

theorem Topology.P2_implies_closure_eq_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hA : Topology.P2 (X := X) A) :
    closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior A) := by
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 (X := X) A :=
    Topology.P2_implies_P1 (X := X) (A := A) hA
  exact Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 (X := X) (A := A) hP1
